Ronald Raphael Coifman is the Phillips <a href="/wiki/Professor" title="Professor">Professor</a> of <a href="/wiki/Mathematics" title="Mathematics">Mathematics</a> at <a href="/wiki/Yale_University" title="Yale University">Yale University</a>. Coifman graduated from the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Geneva" title="University of Geneva">University of Geneva</a> in 1965.
Coifman is a member of the <a href="/wiki/American_Academy_of_Arts_and_Sciences" title="American Academy of Arts and Sciences">American Academy of Arts and Sciences</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Connecticut_Academy_of_Science_and_Engineering" title="Connecticut Academy of Science and Engineering">Connecticut Academy of Science and Engineering</a>, and the <a href="/wiki/United_States_National_Academy_of_Sciences" title="United States National Academy of Sciences" class="mw-redirect">National Academy of Sciences</a>. He is a recipient of the 1996 <a href="/wiki/DARPA" title="DARPA">DARPA</a> Sustained Excellence Award, the 1996 Connecticut Science Medal, the 1999 <a href="/wiki/Pioneer_Award" title="Pioneer Award">Pioneer Award</a> of the International Society for Industrial and Applied Science, and the 1999 <a href="/wiki/National_Medal_of_Science" title="National Medal of Science">National Medal of Science</a>.
.
